overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification for its functionality, data
  collection, and report generation. The agent's initial analysis revealed
  several critical gaps, including the absence of a 1-10 tiredness severity
  scale with safety warnings, lack of explicit detection for Comorbid Insomnia
  and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and the omission of
  weighted scoring for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS). Additionally, the
  reports were missing crucial outbound links to external resources. Following
  this, the agent systematically addressed each identified gap. This involved
  updating data models and validation schemas, enhancing the UI to capture new
  input (like the severity scale), and significantly refining the report
  generation logic for both the web interface and PDF exports to incorporate new
  diagnostic criteria, personalized feedback, and a dedicated section for
  external sleep and mental health resources. The implementation ensured the
  application now more closely aligns with the user's detailed requirements.
